# Auth and RBAC Guardrails

- Keep cookie-based Supabase SSR clients centralized in `lib/supabase/`.
- Middleware must protect role-based routes and avoid bypass paths.
- Any auth redirect must preserve locale and intended destination when possible.
- Profile role lookups must read from `public.profiles` by `auth.uid()`.
- Never grant admin behavior unless role check explicitly confirms `admin`.
- Keep user roles constrained to known values (`admin`, `user`, `canil`).
